glossary={'operators':'Operators are used to perform operations on variables and values.',
    'string':'String is a collection of alphabets, words or other characters',
    'if loop':'Python if Statement is used for decision-making operations',
    'append':'append() will place new items in the available space',
    'insert':'The insert() method inserts the specified value at the specified position.',
    'float':' to represent real numbers with both an integer and fractional component',
    'variable':' symbolic name that is a reference or pointer to an object.',
    'list':'a list is created by placing elements inside square brackets [] , separated by commas.',
    'function':' group of related statements that performs a specific task.',
    'print':'The print() function prints the specified message to the screen, or other standard output device.',
    'input':'Python has an input function which lets you ask a user for some text input.'}
for i,x in glossary.items():
    print('\n',i,':',x)